race.comment: THRILLING VENTURE (5) raced on the speed last start and battled on well but found one better over 1000m at Scone. Has been in solid form this prep with two wins from four starts. Only needs to hold her form to be very competitive. WINGED (3) went fast early and went on to score dominantly last time at Gunnedah. Best figures measure up. Sure to run well. STILLWELL (4) was well beaten by WINGED last start when favourite. Meets the winner a lot better this time at the weights and is drawn well. Can turn the tables. CAMPARI TWIST (1) was almost too bad to be true when having her first race start in NSW. Her form stacks right up though and she's worth another chance. CHICKEN LEGS (9) will likely drift back from the draw and be charging hard late under the light weight. Don't dismiss.
